‚ÄúPocketing‚Äù means holding food in the cheeks or mouth instead of chewing and swallowing. Some children also refuse meals, eat very slowly, or spit food out. This can be frustrating‚Äîand sometimes it can signal a medical issue.

> ‚úÖ **Quick note:** Many children pocket food because of sensory preferences or chewing skill development. But **pocketing + choking/coughing**, **drooling**, **wet/gurgly voice**, **food stuck**, or **poor growth** needs medical assessment.

