## üßæ Quick ‚ÄúAt-a-glance‚Äù box

> ‚úÖ **Topic:** Food pocketing + refusal to eat  
> **Common parent terms:** ‚ÄúHolds food in cheeks,‚Äù ‚Äúchews forever,‚Äù ‚Äúspits it out,‚Äù ‚Äúrefuses solids,‚Äù ‚Äúonly eats soft foods,‚Äù ‚Äúwon‚Äôt swallow meat/bread‚Äù  
>
> **What it is (2‚Äì3 lines):** Pocketing can happen when a child dislikes textures, is still learning chewing skills, feels pain or discomfort when swallowing, or becomes anxious after a scary gag/choke. The goal is to keep meals safe, reduce pressure, and identify when medical or feeding therapy support is needed.  
>
> **Who it affects (typical ages):** Often toddlers and preschoolers, but can occur at any age‚Äîespecially after a choking event or in children with sensory differences.  
>
> ‚úÖ **What parents should do today:**  
