### Common myths vs facts
- **Myth:** ‚ÄúPocketing is always behavior.‚Äù  
  **Fact:** It can be sensory, skill-based, anxiety-related, or medical discomfort.
- **Myth:** ‚ÄúIf they‚Äôre hungry, they‚Äôll eat.‚Äù  
  **Fact:** If swallowing is uncomfortable or scary, hunger doesn‚Äôt always override fear/pain.
- **Myth:** ‚ÄúForce will fix it.‚Äù  
  **Fact:** Pressure often increases refusal and anxiety‚Äîand can increase choking risk.

