## ‚õî What NOT to do (common mistakes)

- Don‚Äôt force ‚Äújust swallow it‚Äù (increases fear and choking risk)  
- Don‚Äôt rush textures too quickly (jumping from puree to tough solids can backfire)  
- Don‚Äôt keep meals going for an hour (fatigue worsens chewing)  
- Don‚Äôt ignore constipation‚Äîlow appetite and nausea can worsen pocketing/refusal  
- Don‚Äôt assume it‚Äôs ‚Äújust picky‚Äù if there are medical clues (food stuck, water-washing, vomiting, weight loss)

