## ‚ùì Parent FAQs

### ‚ÄúIs it contagious?‚Äù
No.

### ‚ÄúCan my child eat ___?‚Äù
Yes‚Äîstart with safe foods and make tiny texture steps. Avoid high-risk choking foods if your child is pocketing frequently.

### ‚ÄúCan they bathe/swim/exercise?‚Äù
Yes.

### ‚ÄúWill they outgrow it?‚Äù
Many children do‚Äîespecially when the cause is sensory/skill development and there are no red flags. Persistent cases benefit from feeding therapy and sometimes medical evaluation.

### ‚ÄúWhen can we stop treatment?‚Äù
When pocketing is rare, meals are calm and efficient, and textures are expanding steadily. If therapy is involved, your team will guide the taper.

